[{"id":"786c2f86-f2d2-4b7b-bd7e-9b0e49b95382","projectId":"d2558169-dfa4-4852-a901-290a994ae6d9","documentId":"ac5a93f0-2f26-48d9-82a6-ed2eea29b840","type":"note","x":-245.827,"y":956.679,"width":658.678,"height":482.219,"zIndex":31,"createdAt":1777545368164,"updatedAt":1777545421893,"data":{"type":"note","content":"<h3 class=\"text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold\">Projectile Motion</h3><p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\">An object thrown at an angle, moving freely under gravity. Path = <strong>parabola</strong>.</p><p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\"><strong>Key idea (Galileo):</strong> Horizontal and vertical motions are <strong>completely independent.</strong></p><div class=\"overflow-x-auto w-full px-2 mb-6\"><table class=\"min-w-full border-collapse text-sm leading-[1.7] whitespace-normal\"><thead class=\"text-left\"><tr><th scope=\"col\" class=\"text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold\">Direction</th><th scope=\"col\" class=\"text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold\">Type</th><th scope=\"col\" class=\"text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold\">Equations</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">Horizontal (x)</td><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">Uniform velocity</td><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">x = u cosθ · t</td></tr><tr><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">Vertical (y)</td><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">Free fall</td><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">y = u sinθ · t − ½gt²</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\"><strong>Important Formulas:</strong></p><p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\">\n</p><div class=\"overflow-x-auto w-full px-2 mb-6\"><table class=\"min-w-full border-collapse text-sm leading-[1.7] whitespace-normal\"><thead class=\"text-left\"><tr><th scope=\"col\" class=\"text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold\">Quantity</th><th scope=\"col\" class=\"text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold\">Formula</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">Time of Flight</td><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">T = 2u sinθ / g</td></tr><tr><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">Maximum Height</td><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">H = u² sin²θ / 2g</td></tr><tr><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">Horizontal Range</td><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">R = u² sin2θ / g</td></tr><tr><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">Max Range (at 45°)</td><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">R_max = u²/g</td></tr><tr><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">Trajectory (path)</td><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">y = x tanθ − gx² / (2u² cos²θ)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","color":"#dbeafe","sourceExcerpt":"3.6 Projectile Motion","sourcePageNumber":8}},{"id":"ab959df6-f5fa-44b5-ad39-9427f421532e","projectId":"d2558169-dfa4-4852-a901-290a994ae6d9","documentId":"ac5a93f0-2f26-48d9-82a6-ed2eea29b840","type":"note","x":-315.155,"y":1640.43,"width":505.835,"height":235.598,"zIndex":1777545446674,"createdAt":1777545446666,"updatedAt":1777545459818,"data":{"type":"note","content":"<h3 class=\"text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold\">Common Misconceptions (Exam Traps)</h3><p>\n</p><ul class=\"[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3\">\n<li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2\">Centripetal force is <strong>NOT a new force</strong> — it's the net inward force provided by tension/gravity/friction depending on situation</li>\n<li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2\">If centripetal force is removed, object flies off <strong>tangentially</strong> (not outward!)</li>\n<li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2\">At highest point of projectile, only <strong>vy = 0</strong>, not total velocity</li>\n<li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2\">UCM object <strong>is accelerating</strong> (direction changes), even though speed is constant</li>\n<li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2\">Never add vectors as plain numbers — always use vector laws</li></ul>","color":"yellow","sourceExcerpt":null,"sourcePageNumber":null}},{"id":"aedb559d-7108-4c9f-be97-dbcd957fd870","projectId":"d2558169-dfa4-4852-a901-290a994ae6d9","documentId":"ac5a93f0-2f26-48d9-82a6-ed2eea29b840","type":"note","x":-442.889,"y":-531.556,"width":490.286,"height":320.199,"zIndex":6,"createdAt":1777545051276,"updatedAt":1777545068348,"data":{"type":"note","content":"<div><div class=\"standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3\"><h3 class=\"text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold\">Scalars vs Vectors</h3></div></div><div><div class=\"standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3\"><div class=\"overflow-x-auto w-full px-2 mb-6\"><table class=\"min-w-full border-collapse text-sm leading-[1.7] whitespace-normal\"><thead class=\"text-left\"><tr><th scope=\"col\" class=\"text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold\">Scalars</th><th scope=\"col\" class=\"text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold\">Vectors</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">Only magnitude</td><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">Magnitude + Direction</td></tr><tr><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">Mass, Speed, Time, Energy</td><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">Displacement, Velocity, Force, Acceleration</td></tr><tr><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">Ordinary algebra</td><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">Vector algebra (triangle/parallelogram law)</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></div><div><div class=\"standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3\"><blockquote class=\"ml-2 border-l-4 border-border-300/10 pl-4 text-text-300\">\n<p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\">⚠️ Electric current has direction but is <strong>scalar</strong> — it doesn't obey vector addition laws (Kirchhoff's law, not triangle law).</p></blockquote></div></div>","color":"#dbeafe","sourceExcerpt":"3.1 Scalars and Vectors\n3.1.1 Definitions","sourcePageNumber":2}},{"id":"b60d445d-3f2e-4c60-a592-d69757bc6e5f","projectId":"d2558169-dfa4-4852-a901-290a994ae6d9","documentId":"ac5a93f0-2f26-48d9-82a6-ed2eea29b840","type":"note","x":-186.814,"y":2016.91,"width":514.937,"height":215.573,"zIndex":1777545465754,"createdAt":1777545465748,"updatedAt":1777545493356,"data":{"type":"note","content":"<h3 class=\"text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold\">Quick-Recall Formulas</h3><p>\n</p><div role=\"group\" aria-label=\"Code\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"relative group/copy bg-bg-000/50 border-0.5 border-border-400 rounded-lg focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-accent-100\"><div class=\"sticky opacity-0 group-hover/copy:opacity-100 group-focus-within/copy:opacity-100 top-2 py-2 h-12 w-0 float-right\"><div class=\"absolute right-0 h-8 px-2 items-center inline-flex z-10\"><button class=\"inline-flex\n  items-center\n  justify-center\n  relative\n  isolate\n  shrink-0\n  can-focus\n  select-none\n  disabled:pointer-events-none\n  disabled:opacity-50\n  disabled:shadow-none\n  disabled:drop-shadow-none border-transparent\n          transition\n          font-base\n          duration-300\n          ease-[cubic-bezier(0.165,0.85,0.45,1)] h-8 w-8 rounded-md backdrop-blur-md _fill_10ocf_9 _ghost_10ocf_96\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Copy to clipboard\" data-state=\"closed\"><div class=\"relative\"><div class=\"transition-all opacity-100 scale-100\" style=\"width: 20px; height: 20px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"currentColor\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"transition-all opacity-100 scale-100\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"flex-shrink: 0;\"><path d=\"M12.5 3A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 14 4.5V6h1.5A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 17 7.5v8a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-1.5 1.5h-8A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 6 15.5V14H4.5A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 3 12.5v-8A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 4.5 3zm1.5 9.5a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-1.5 1.5H7v1.5a.5.5 0 0 0 .5.5h8a.5.5 0 0 0 .5-.5v-8a.5.5 0 0 0-.5-.5H14zM4.5 4a.5.5 0 0 0-.5.5v8a.5.5 0 0 0 .5.5h8a.5.5 0 0 0 .5-.5v-8a.5.5 0 0 0-.5-.5z\"></path></svg></div><div class=\"absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center\"><div class=\"transition-all opacity-0 scale-50\" style=\"width: 20px; height: 20px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"currentColor\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"transition-all opacity-0 scale-50\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"flex-shrink: 0;\"><path d=\"M15.188 5.11a.5.5 0 0 1 .752.626l-.056.084-7.5 9a.5.5 0 0 1-.738.033l-3.5-3.5-.064-.078a.501.501 0 0 1 .693-.693l.078.064 3.113 3.113 7.15-8.58z\"></path></svg></div></div></div></button></div></div><div class=\"overflow-x-auto\"><pre class=\"code-block__code !my-0 !rounded-lg !text-sm !leading-relaxed p-3.5\" style=\"color: rgb(234, 236, 240); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><code style=\"background: transparent; font-family: var(--font-mono); white-space: pre-wrap;\">R = √(A² + B² + 2AB cosθ)     ← resultant of two vectors\nAx = A cosθ,  Ay = A sinθ      ← resolution\nT = 2u sinθ/g                  ← time of flight\nH = u²sin²θ/2g                 ← max height  \nR = u²sin2θ/g                  ← range\nac = v²/r = ω²r                ← centripetal acceleration\nv = ωr                         ← linear ↔ angular speed</code></pre></div></div>","color":"yellow","sourceExcerpt":null,"sourcePageNumber":null}},{"id":"d2ef1a02-b68f-4d38-b86c-91bb586080f2","projectId":"d2558169-dfa4-4852-a901-290a994ae6d9","documentId":"ac5a93f0-2f26-48d9-82a6-ed2eea29b840","type":"note","x":-294.069,"y":-79.4059,"width":447.506,"height":467.655,"zIndex":16,"createdAt":1777545171388,"updatedAt":1777545237850,"data":{"type":"note","content":"<h3 class=\"text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold\">Vector Addition Laws</h3><p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\"><strong>Triangle Law</strong> — Place vectors head-to-tail; resultant = tail of first to head of last.</p><p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\"><strong>Parallelogram Law</strong> — Two vectors from same point form adjacent sides; resultant = diagonal.</p><p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\"><strong>Formula:</strong> R = √(A² + B² + 2AB cosθ), direction: tan α = B sinθ / (A + B cosθ)</p><p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\"><strong>Special Cases:</strong></p><div class=\"overflow-x-auto w-full px-2 mb-6\"><table class=\"min-w-full border-collapse text-sm leading-[1.7] whitespace-normal\"><thead class=\"text-left\"><tr><th scope=\"col\" class=\"text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold\">Angle θ</th><th scope=\"col\" class=\"text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold\">Resultant</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">0° (same direction)</td><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">R = A + B (maximum)</td></tr><tr><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">180° (opposite)</td><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">R = |A − B| (minimum)</td></tr><tr><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">90° (perpendicular)</td><td class=\"border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top\">R = √(A² + B²)</td></tr></tbody></table></div><blockquote class=\"ml-2 border-l-4 border-border-300/10 pl-4 text-text-300\">\n<p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\"><strong>Example:</strong> 6 N and 8 N forces → at 0°: <strong>14 N</strong>, at 90°: <strong>10 N</strong>, at 180°: <strong>2 N</strong>, at 60°: <strong>≈12.2 N</strong></p>\n</blockquote><p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n</p><p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\"><strong>Vector Subtraction:</strong> A⃗ − B⃗ = A⃗ + (−B⃗), magnitude = √(A² + B² − 2AB cosθ)</p>","color":"#dbeafe","sourceExcerpt":"3.3.2 Vector Addition — Parallelogram Law","sourcePageNumber":5}},{"id":"ec7d3325-a848-4658-a09f-fb06cc96e00f","projectId":"d2558169-dfa4-4852-a901-290a994ae6d9","documentId":"ac5a93f0-2f26-48d9-82a6-ed2eea29b840","type":"note","x":-254.374,"y":471.884,"width":535.798,"height":385.735,"zIndex":23,"createdAt":1777545307967,"updatedAt":1777545335710,"data":{"type":"note","content":"<h3 class=\"text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold\">Resolution of Vectors</h3><p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\">Splitting one vector into perpendicular components along x and y axes.</p><ul class=\"[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3\">\n<li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2\"><strong>Ax = A cosθ</strong> (horizontal component)</li>\n<li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2\"><strong>Ay = A sinθ</strong> (vertical component)</li>\n<li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2\"><strong>Back to magnitude:</strong> A = √(Ax² + Ay²)</li>\n<li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2\"><strong>Angle:</strong> θ = tan⁻¹(Ay / Ax)</li>\n</ul><blockquote class=\"ml-2 border-l-4 border-border-300/10 pl-4 text-text-300\">\n<p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\"><strong>Example:</strong> 10 N force at 60° → Fx = 10 cos60° = <strong>5 N</strong>, Fy = 10 sin60° = <strong>8.66 N</strong></p>\n</blockquote><p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\"><strong>Trig values to memorize:</strong></p><p>\n\n\n\n\n</p><ul class=\"[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3\">\n<li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2\">sin/cos 30° = 0.5 / 0.866</li>\n<li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2\">sin/cos 37° ≈ 0.6 / 0.8 <em>(3-4-5 triangle)</em></li>\n<li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2\">sin/cos 45° = 0.707 / 0.707</li>\n<li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2\">sin/cos 53° ≈ 0.8 / 0.6</li>\n<li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words pl-2\">sin/cos 60° = 0.866 / 0.5</li></ul>","color":"#dbeafe","sourceExcerpt":"3.4 Resolution of Vectors","sourcePageNumber":6}}]